{"parentUuid":"4bb14f70-ed78-49d4-bf68-1a0347c25e7b","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/ryan/formal-conjectures","sessionId":"3e572dae-f190-430e-b82e-aabd837c8df1","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"ai-erdos-7","agentId":"a4aaa4dde3be32f19","slug":"quizzical-drifting-clarke","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013aforfXrakor3QhGVgDCx7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/-\n     2→Copyright 2026 The Formal Conjectures Authors.\n     3→\n     4→Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→\n     8→    https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→\n    10→Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→limitations under the License.\n    15→-/\n    16→\n    17→import FormalConjectures.Util.ProblemImports\n    18→\n    19→/-!\n    20→# Erdős Problem 764\n    21→\n    22→*Reference:* [erdosproblems.com/764](https://www.erdosproblems.com/764)\n    23→\n    24→A conjecture of Erdős [Er65b][Er70c] on whether the partial sums of the 3-fold additive\n    25→convolution $1_A \\ast 1_A \\ast 1_A$ can have bounded error term around a linear function.\n    26→Related to problem 763, which concerns the 2-fold convolution.\n    27→\n    28→Disproved by Vaughan [Va72], who proved the answer is no in a strong form, showing that even\n    29→$\\sum_{n \\leq N} 1_A \\ast 1_A \\ast 1_A(n) = cN + o(N^{1/4} / (\\log N)^{1/2})$ is impossible.\n    30→-/\n    31→\n    32→open Finset BigOperators Classical\n    33→\n    34→namespace Erdos764\n    35→\n    36→/-- The number of representations of $n$ as $a_1 + a_2 + a_3$ with\n    37→$a_1, a_2, a_3 \\in A$, i.e., the 3-fold additive convolution\n    38→$1_A \\ast 1_A \\ast 1_A(n)$. -/\n    39→noncomputable def repCount764 (A : Set ℕ) (n : ℕ) : ℕ :=\n    40→  ((Finset.range (n + 1) ×ˢ Finset.range (n + 1)).filter\n    41→    (fun p => p.1 + p.2 ≤ n ∧ p.1 ∈ A ∧ p.2 ∈ A ∧ (n - p.1 - p.2) ∈ A)).card\n    42→\n    43→/-- The partial sum $\\sum_{n=0}^{N} 1_A \\ast 1_A \\ast 1_A(n)$. -/\n    44→noncomputable def repSum764 (A : Set ℕ) (N : ℕ) : ℕ :=\n    45→  (Finset.range (N + 1)).sum (fun n => repCount764 A n)\n    46→\n    47→/--\n    48→Erdős Problem 764 (Vaughan's theorem) [Va72]:\n    49→\n    50→There do not exist $A \\subseteq \\mathbb{N}$ and $c > 0$ such that\n    51→$\\sum_{n \\leq N} 1_A \\ast 1_A \\ast 1_A(n) = cN + O(1)$.\n    52→-/\n    53→@[category research solved, AMS 11]\n    54→theorem erdos_764 : answer(False) ↔\n    55→    ∃ (A : Set ℕ) (c : ℝ), c > 0 ∧\n    56→      ∃ C : ℝ, ∀ N : ℕ, |↑(repSum764 A N) - c * ↑N| ≤ C := by\n    57→  sorry\n    58→\n    59→end Erdos764\n    60→"}]},"uuid":"d5c4dc42-4041-4c9d-947a-991c8e14649f","timestamp":"2026-03-10T23:58:24.228Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"4bb14f70-ed78-49d4-bf68-1a0347c25e7b"}
